<TITLE> Rajuk plots deadline stretched to Jan 15 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 17 (bdnews24.com)  Dhaka city development authority Rajuk has extended the deadline for application for housing plots in Uttara, Purbachal to Jan. 15, housing and public works secretary SM Rashidul Hye told bdnews24.com on Wednesday. On Monday, the housing and public works ministry in a press release said applicants for the plots may pay Tk 150 court fees instead of non-judicial stamps for their affidavits. The decision was taken due to the dearth of Tk 150 non-judicial stamps. Rajuk had asked applicants to file affidavits using Tk 150 non-judicial stamps, but vendors taking advantage of their scarcity have been selling a Tk 150 stamp for Tk 1000, the press release said
